# Coding Standards — MUST-Comply

**NeNe Contact inherits NENE2's coding conventions.** Binding docs in
`docs/development/`: `coding-standards.md` (index), `naming-conventions.md`,
`backend-standards.md`, `frontend-standards.md`, `nene2-compliance.md`. NENE2
`docs/development/` is the upstream source of truth; the Contact doc wins where they
differ, NENE2 applies where Contact is silent.

Before writing PHP, OpenAPI, SQL/migrations, or frontend code, read the relevant doc.

## Merge blockers (backend)

- Missing `declare(strict_types=1);`; non-`final` app classes; mutable DTOs
- Business logic in a Handler/middleware; SQL outside a `Pdo*Repository`
- Layer-first folders (`src/Handlers/`, `src/Repositories/`, `src/UseCases/`)
- Raw arrays/PSR-7 passed into a UseCase (must be typed readonly DTOs)
- Reinventing a NENE2 object (responses, routing, pagination, auth, DB, validation)
- camelCase in public JSON; renamed shipped `operationId`; unregistered identifier
- Error responses leaking stack traces/SQL/secrets/PII; not RFC 9457 Problem Details
- Tenant-scoped query not filtered by `organization_id` (multi-tenancy.md, ADR 0006/0014); cross-tenant access outside superadmin

## Merge blockers (frontend)

- Upward or cross-feature imports; placement-matrix violations; deep slice imports
- `fetch` outside `shared/api/client.ts`; TanStack logic outside entity files
- `any`; default exports; raw color/spacing/type literals outside `shared/ui/theme/`
- Embed widget holding an admin JWT, running operator JS, `eval`, or un-isolated styles
- Locale beyond `ja`/`en`; hardcoded user-facing strings

## Layering (the spine)

`HTTP handler (thin) → UseCase (execute, invariants) → RepositoryInterface → Pdo*Repository`.
Group by domain concept. Frontend: `app → pages → features → entities → shared` — no
arrow points upward.

A justified deviation requires an **ADR** (self-authority, ADR 0012 model) — never a silent
exception.
